Sit.

530
00:33:08,487 --> 00:33:10,422
Does that mean you're in?

531
00:33:10,456 --> 00:33:11,990
Yeah.

532
00:33:12,024 --> 00:33:13,659
[Frank] Alright, you
got any other questions?

533
00:33:13,692 --> 00:33:15,694
[Ronnie] Yeah, I
got one question.

534
00:33:15,727 --> 00:33:18,297
Me and my brother, we heard
a couple of things about you.

535
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:21,133
We need you to
clear it up for us.

536
00:33:21,167 --> 00:33:22,901
You heard some
things like what?

537
00:33:22,934 --> 00:33:26,238
[Vic] That whoever
works these jobs of yours,

538
00:33:26,272 --> 00:33:28,707
They never get seen again.

539
00:33:30,342 --> 00:33:32,778
Let me tell you
something, fellas.

540
00:33:32,811 --> 00:33:37,216
People talk all the time, they
talk for a lot of reasons.

541
00:33:37,249 --> 00:33:41,120
Envy, jealousy, greed.

542
00:33:41,153 --> 00:33:42,754
All you need to
know is if you're

543
00:33:42,788 --> 00:33:46,325
Square with me, I'll
be square with you.

544
00:33:46,358 --> 00:33:48,227
I'll be in touch.

545
00:34:05,777 --> 00:34:07,213
Hi!

546
00:34:07,679 --> 00:34:08,647
How you doing?

547
00:34:08,680 --> 00:34:10,116
You're new here.

548
00:34:10,149 --> 00:34:12,784
I'm Jackie.

549
00:34:12,818 --> 00:34:15,387
Well, actually, we met
the other day, kind of.

550
00:34:15,421 --> 00:34:18,124
Yeah, what's yours again?

551
00:34:18,157 --> 00:34:18,990
What?

552
00:34:19,024 --> 00:34:21,227
Your name, dumb-dumb.

553
00:34:22,628 --> 00:34:23,662
Oscar.

554
00:34:23,695 --> 00:34:26,232
Oscar Kissell.

555
00:34:26,265 --> 00:34:27,866
[Jackie] So what
are you hoping to be?

556
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:30,869
A mystery writer or something?

557
00:34:30,902 --> 00:34:32,338
I don't know.

558
00:34:33,105 --> 00:34:35,707
Oh my God, is that typed?

559
00:34:35,741 --> 00:34:37,443
Do you...

560
00:34:37,476 --> 00:34:39,111
You used the typewriter.

561
00:34:39,145 --> 00:34:41,180
I didn't even know they
were around anymore.

562
00:34:41,213 --> 00:34:42,548
I like typewriters.

563
00:34:42,581 --> 00:34:43,315
I mean, I like things...

564
00:34:43,349 --> 00:34:44,816
Hey, what's that?

565
00:34:44,850 --> 00:34:46,318
Oh!

566
00:34:47,886 --> 00:34:50,356
Gotcha.

567
00:34:50,389 --> 00:34:53,925
Okay, class, everybody
take their seats.

568
00:34:53,959 --> 00:34:56,027
We're gonna start.

569
00:35:00,899 --> 00:35:04,736
[Voiceover] Monday,
late afternoon.

570
00:35:04,770 --> 00:35:06,772
Diamond district.

571
00:35:06,805 --> 00:35:11,109
And Frank Stone gets ready.

572
00:35:15,013 --> 00:35:20,386
A large Romanian man
