00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:39,671
(Speaks Romanian)

576
00:35:40,639 --> 00:35:43,141
You two midgets
think you can rob me?

577
00:35:43,175 --> 00:35:45,177
Try it.

578
00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:59,191
[Vic] Jesus Christ,
there's a fortune in here!

579
00:35:59,225 --> 00:36:00,359
[Ronnie] Nice!

580
00:36:00,392 --> 00:36:02,661
Grab the bag, let's
get out of here.

581
00:36:06,532 --> 00:36:08,834
I think there's only
enough for me and my brother.

582
00:36:08,867 --> 00:36:10,068
What?

583
00:36:10,101 --> 00:36:11,270
[Vic] You heard me,
you dirty double...

584
00:36:13,772 --> 00:36:16,708
[Frank] It's called
the double-cross.

585
00:36:16,742 --> 00:36:19,945
Or the dirty double-cross.

586
00:36:19,978 --> 00:36:21,380
Someone turning on
you is one of the

587
00:36:21,413 --> 00:36:25,217
Unfortunate hazards
in this line of work.

588
00:36:25,251 --> 00:36:30,289
Luckily for Frank, he's
always expecting it.

589
00:36:30,322 --> 00:36:32,190
[Mr. Benson] Wow,
that's interesting.

590
00:36:33,625 --> 00:36:37,529
It really is getting more
and more cohesive, Oscar.

591
00:36:37,563 --> 00:36:39,197
Keep it up.

592
00:36:52,110 --> 00:36:55,414
Hey, hey Oscar!

593
00:36:56,882 --> 00:36:58,350
Hey!

594
00:37:02,254 --> 00:37:05,324
Well, I was just wondering if
you wanted to get a coffee?

595
00:37:06,592 --> 00:37:08,960
So, I just wanted to know what

596
00:37:08,994 --> 00:37:11,397
Goes on in that head of yours.

597
00:37:13,265 --> 00:37:14,700
What do you mean?

598
00:37:14,733 --> 00:37:20,238
[Jackie] Well, how do you get
your stuff to sound so real?

599
00:37:20,272 --> 00:37:23,208
I don't know, I just...

600
00:37:23,241 --> 00:37:28,013
I feel like I'm in the same
world as your characters.

601
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:30,382
It's...

602
00:37:30,416 --> 00:37:31,617
I don't know.

603
00:37:31,650 --> 00:37:34,152
I just write whatever
comes into my head.

604
00:37:36,855 --> 00:37:41,827
Wow, I mean, Frank
Stone is so cold.

605
00:37:44,896 --> 00:37:47,966
He has a lot of
demons in his past.

606
00:37:49,134 --> 00:37:51,770
They're going to stay there
until he gets rid of 'em.

607
00:37:53,939 --> 00:37:56,107
He doesn't trust anyone.

608
00:37:57,309 --> 00:37:59,311
That's how he survives.

609
00:38:02,414 --> 00:38:05,951
[Jackie] Have you always
had this kind of imagination?

610
00:38:05,984 --> 00:38:07,018
Did you read those recommended

611
00:38:07,052 --> 00:38:09,120
Books the teacher
told us about?

612
00:38:09,154 --> 00:38:11,890
I didn't read anything.

613
00:38:11,923 --> 00:38:14,125
You're so serious!

614
00:38:14,159 --> 00:38:15,894
But you're modest, too.

615
00:38:15,927 --> 00:38:18,830
Can you pass me the sugar?

616
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:22,534
Boo!

617
00:38:24,102 --> 00:38:26,071
Oh, sorry.

618
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:30,742
(Horn honks)

619
00:38:35,514 --> 00:38:38,249
Thanks for giving me
a ride home, Oscar.

620
00:38:39,551 --> 00:38:41,953
That was nice.

621
00:38:43,121 --> 00:38:44,890
Well...

622
00:38:46,091 --> 00:38:51,062
When did you start dressing
like a little tugboat captain?

623
00:38:55,100 --> 00:38:59,137
You know, do you
like the open sea?

624
00:39:01,973 --> 00:39:03,509
Hello?

625
00:39:03,542 --> 00:39:05,343
Yeah, you...

626
00:39:05,377 --> 00:39:07,245
You don't give that much.

627
00:39:07,278 --> 00:39:10,081
You really don't
talk that much.

628
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,023
Oh.

629
00:39:20,025 --> 00:39:21,226
Are you hungry?

630
00:39:21,259 --> 00:39:22,260
Why don't you come
upstairs and let me

631
00:39:22,293 --> 00:39:25,163
Make you a
fluffernutter sandwich.

632
00:39:26,064 --> 00:39:27,799
Have you ever had one?

633
00:39:27,833 --> 00:39:29,034
I can tell you haven't had one,

634
00:39:29,067 --> 00:39:32,237
Cause your eyes didn't
light up when I said it.

635
00:39:34,072 --> 00:39:36,174
You're missing out.

636
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:41,112
Do you want a beer?

637
00:39:41,146 --> 00:39:42,113
No thanks.

638
00:39:42,147 --> 00:39:44,282
I don't drink.

639
00:39:44,315 --> 00:39:46,251
[Jackie] You don't drink?

640
00:39:47,853 --> 00:39:49,087
Yeesh.

641
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:51,156
What are you, a boy
scout or something?

642
00:39:51,189 --> 00:39:52,858
How about a glass of milk?

643
00:39:52,891 --> 00:39:54,993
[Frank] That sounds good.

644
00:40:03,301 --> 00:40:03,935
[Jackie] Here you go.

645
00:40:03,969 --> 00:40:06,204
(Horses whinny)

646
00:40:10,141 --> 00:40:12,978
What's the matter, Oscar?

647
00:40:13,011 --> 00:40:14,680
I don't know.

648
00:40:14,713 --> 00:40:17,215
Something strange
just happened.

649
00:40:17,248 --> 00:40:19,518
[Jackie] What?

650
00:40:19,551 --> 00:40:22,220
The horse on the glass
here reminded me of

651
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:25,423
Something that happened
to me when I was a kid.

652
00:40:27,058 --> 00:40:30,896
You know I was raised
in an orphanage.

653
00:40:30,929 --> 00:40:34,600
And one day, me and
all the other boys

654
00:40:34,633 --> 00:40:37,703
We were all taken
on a field trip.

655
00:40:37,736 --> 00:40:41,006
But when the bus got
there, the first thing

656
00:40:41,039 --> 00:40:46,978
That I saw was this
beautiful Grey horse.

657
00:40:47,012 --> 00:40:49,314
So I approached the
horse really slowly

658
00:40:49,347 --> 00:40:54,319
And I was talking to him
softly, the way a kid would.

659
00:40:55,487 --> 00:40:58,323
And all of a sudden,
the horse, he went nuts.

660
00:40:58,356 --> 00:41:00,425
I mean, he went
totally haywire.

661
00:41:00,458 --> 00:41:05,531
Started jumping up on
his hind legs, kicking.

662
00:41:05,564 --> 00:41:06,732
He broke free from the chain

663
00:41:06,765 --> 00:41:09,835
And he started to
scare the other horses.

664
00:41:09,868 --> 00:41:14,305
Well, horses do weird
things like that sometimes.

665
00:41:14,339 --> 00:41:17,909
Yeah, well the
headmaster, he got so angry

666
00:41:17,943 --> 00:41:20,912
That he grabbed me and he
started to beat me publicly,

667
00:41:20,946 --> 00:41:23,181
Right in front of
the other boys.

668
00:41:23,214 --> 00:41:26,384
That headmaster
sounds like such a jerk!

669
00:41:26,417 --> 00:41:30,288
And after that, all the
kids, they laughed at me.

670
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:34,392
They humiliated me, mocked me.

671
00:41:34,425 --> 00:41:37,428
And I'll tell you
that headmaster...

672
00:41:37,462 --> 00:41:39,731
After that, he never
missed an opportunity...

673
00:41:39,765 --> 00:41:43,134
Let's change the subject,
talk about something else.

674
00:41:57,348 --> 00:41:59,117
Hey, Oscar?

675
00:41:59,150 --> 00:42:04,255
(Laughing)

676
00:42:04,289 --> 00:42:05,090
Isn't it funny?

677
00:42:05,123 --> 00:42:06,524
I'm leaving.

678
00:42:06,558 --> 00:42:08,093
[Jackie] Oh, come on.

679
00:42:08,126 --> 00:42:09,327
What's the matter with you?

680
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:11,296
Listen, you may think
everything is a joke.

681
00:42:11,329 --> 00:42:14,099
But me, I take
everything seriously.

682
00:42:14,132 --> 00:42:16,267
And I don't appreciate
you mocking me.

683
00:42:16,301 --> 00:42:18,469
[Jackie] I wasn't
mocking you.

684
00:42:18,503 --> 00:42:20,572
What's the matter with you?

685
00:42:20,606 --> 00:42:22,207
I...

686
00:42:22,841 --> 00:42:26,011
(Overlapping conversation)

687
00:42:32,183 --> 00:42:35,654
[Vinny] Oh, look who it is!

688
00:42:37,488 --> 00:42:40,391
It's Mr. Personality!

689
00:42:40,425 --> 00:42:43,929
He came here to brighten up
everybody's day, now didn't ya?

690
00:42:43,962 --> 00:42:46,598
I got a question
for you, scumbag.

691
00:42:46,632 --> 00:42:51,603
How come you make everybody
sick at the very sight of you?

692
00:42:54,072 --> 00:42:55,641
You got the
personality of a cobra

693
00:42:55,674 --> 00:42:57,408
And I've had it up
to here with that.

694
00:42:57,442 --> 00:42:59,911
Come on, Vinny, knock it off.

695
00:42:59,945 --> 00:43:02,013
Sit down!

696
00:43:02,047 --> 00:43:04,950
You have to excuse Vinny,
Frank.

697
00:43:06,184 --> 00:43:09,087
Anyway, how are you
doing today, Frank?

698
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:10,488
Doing good, Tony.

699
00:43:10,521 --> 00:43:12,157
Can I get you
anything to eat?

700
00:43:12,190 --> 00:43:13,959
You don't have to be shy,
we have plenty of food.

701
00:43:13,992 --> 00:43:15,093
More coming out.

702
00:43:15,126 --> 00:43:17,395
No thanks, I'm not hungry.

703
00:43:17,428 --> 00:43:19,364
No?

704
00:43:19,397 --> 00:43:22,100
Give him his freakin' money,
let him get out of here.

705
00:43:29,174 --> 00:43:30,308
[Frank] Thanks.

706
00:43:30,341 --> 00:43:32,577
Oh, oh, Frankie, Frankie.

707
00:43:32,610 --> 00:43:34,445
You know, not for nothing,

708
00:43:34,479 --> 00:43:36,848
But we offer you
food all the time.

709
00:43:36,882 --> 00:43:41,419
And never once, once, do you
everysit down and eat with us.

710
00:43:41,452 --> 00:43:42,921
What's the matter?

711
00:43:42,954 --> 00:43:46,391
My gesture of friendship
doesn't agree with you?

712
00:43:47,959 --> 00:43:51,830
Look at me when I'm
talking to you, Frankie.

713
00:43:53,231 --> 00:43:56,634
Now I want to know why you
think you're too good for us.

714
00:43:56,668 --> 00:43:58,036
Look, it's not that, Tony.

715
00:43:58,069 --> 00:43:59,637
It's just, you know,
I got some place

716
00:43:59,671 --> 00:44:02,007
I got to be in a hurry.

717
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:03,374
Hurry?

718
00:44:03,408 --> 00:44:05,877
Where you got to be, Frankie?

719
00:44:05,911 --> 00:44:07,112
Somewhere.

720
00:44:07,145 --> 00:44:08,313
[Tony] Frank.

721
00:44:08,346 --> 00:44:09,447
The only place
you should ever be

722
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:11,850
In a hurry to get to is home.

723
00:44:11,883 --> 00:44:13,584
Cause home is where
the family is.

724
00:44:13,618 --> 00:44:14,953
Here, look, let me show this.

725
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:17,522
This is my family, alright?

726
00:44:17,555 --> 00:44:19,357
This is my wife, my kids when

727
00:44:19,390 --> 00:44:21,993
They were younger,
my grandkids.

728
00:44:22,027 --> 00:44:24,129
And this, this is the
most cherished picture

729
00:44:24,162 --> 00:44:28,099
I have of my father,
God rest his soul.

730
00:44:29,434 --> 00:44:33,404
You know, I loved him more than
any son ever loved a father.

731
00:44:35,473 --> 00:44:37,242
What about you, Frankie?

732
00:44:37,275 --> 00:44:38,710
Do you have any
pictures of loved

733
00:44:38,744 --> 00:44:41,980
Ones you'd like to show us?

734
00:44:43,114 --> 00:44:44,349
No?

735
00:44:44,382 --> 00:44:45,851
Why not?

736
00:44:45,884 --> 00:44:48,619
You're always in such a
hurry, I would think that

737
00:44:48,653 --> 00:44:52,724
You had hundreds, hundreds
of pictures to show us.

738
00:44:56,261 --> 00:44:58,663
Now the next time that
I ask you to sit down

739
00:44:58,696 --> 00:45:03,001
And eat with us, make
sure you have the time.

740
00:45:03,034 --> 00:45:05,904
Alright, now get the
hell out of here.

741
00:45:05,937 --> 00:45:07,072
Thanks, Tony.

742
00:45:07,105 --> 00:45:08,940
What did you say?

743
00:45:08,974 --> 00:45:11,009
What did you just mumble?

744
00:45:11,709 --> 00:45:13,711
I said thanks, Tony.

745
00:45:16,447 --> 00:45:19,117
[Tony] So, anyway,
about this weekend...

746
00:45:28,126 --> 00:45:32,497
(Piano music)

747
00:45:36,367 --> 00:45:37,568
[Voiceover] There's
nothing more frustrating

748
00:45:37,602 --> 00:45:40,038
Than a man who just
can't express himself.

749
00:45:40,071 --> 00:45:42,841
You know, tell you
how he feels.

750
00:45:43,942 --> 00:45:48,479
That makes him no
different than a lamp.

751
00:45:48,513 --> 00:45:51,382
Or a clay pigeon.

752
00:45:51,416 --> 00:45:56,354
Yeah, clay pigeon, waiting
to get blown up into pieces.

753
00:45:57,588 --> 00:45:58,957
Maybe that's why.

754
00:45:58,990 --> 00:46:03,128
Maybe that's the root
behind Frank Stone's rage.

755
00:46:06,031 --> 00:46:10,101
He just lives,
second to second.

756
00:46:10,135 --> 00:46:12,037
Minute to minute.

757
00:46:12,070 --> 00:46:14,005
Murder to murder.

758
00:46:15,140 --> 00:46:17,408
Like an alcoholic.

759
00:46:17,442 --> 00:46:20,178
Just one day at a time.

760
00:46:23,414 --> 00:46:25,216
That's my boy.

